  "title": "Search Facet Filter value with . in name",
  "body": "## 🐛 Bug description\r\n\r\n<!-- A clear and concise description of what the bug is. -->\r\nI have a facet filer for organization names in my index. It works perfectly fine for all values except those with '.' in their names. I have a name like 'Film.ua group'. I tried searching it in algolia facet search directly and it does not return the name. \r\n\r\n## 🔍 Bug reproduction\r\n\r\n1. Add a facet filer names organization.name\r\n2. Add a value with a . like \"Film.ua group\".\r\n2. Go to the index page on algolia and click on the search icon besides the facet filer. Type the above name. No result is returned.\r\n\r\n## 🖥 Screenshots\r\n\r\n![Capture1Updated](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/11632461/90711969-92ad5a80-e2d4-11ea-93a8-8f4c48282c23.png)\r\n![Capture2Updated](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/11632461/90712131-e91a9900-e2d4-11ea-9211-06b949c4e24e.png)\r\n![Capture3](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/11632461/90712137-eae45c80-e2d4-11ea-86af-b8e9d9e8590a.PNG)\r\n",
